<h2>Encryption vs Encoding vs Hashing</h2>

| Aspect                     | Encryption                                  | Encoding                                              | Hashing                                 |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| **Definition**             | Secure transformation of data using a key   | Data transformation for compatibility or transmission | One-way transformation of data          |
| **Primary Purpose**        | Protect confidentiality                     | Ensure proper data format and transmission            | Verify data integrity                   |
| **Security Provided**      | ✅ Yes                                      | ❌ No                                                 | ✅ Yes                                  |
| **Reversibility**          | Reversible with the correct key             | Fully reversible                                      | Irreversible                            |
| **Key Required**           | Yes (secret or public/private key)          | No                                                    | No                                      |
| **Output Length**          | Variable                                    | Variable                                              | Fixed                                   |
| **Algorithms / Examples**  | AES, RSA, Blowfish                          | Base64, ASCII, UTF-8                                  | SHA-256, SHA-1, MD5                     |
| **Common Use Cases**       | Secure communication, file protection, VPNs | Email transfer, data storage, character encoding      | Password storage, file integrity checks |
| **Data Recovery Possible** | Yes (with key)                              | Yes                                                   | No                                      |
